---
import LandingLayout from '../../layouts/LandingLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/landing/Header.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../../components/landing/SiteFooter.astro';

const repo = 'https://github.com/Goloom-App/goloom';
// Keep this in sync with substantive changes to the policy below.
const lastUpdated = '7 July 2026';
---

<LandingLayout
	title="goloom — privacy policy"
	description="How the goloom website handles data. No cookies, no analytics, no tracking — a short, honest privacy notice."
>
	<Header />
	<main>
		<section class="lp-section">
			<div class="lp-container lp-legal">
				<h1>Privacy policy</h1>
				<p class="lp-legal__meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

				<p>
					This notice explains what happens to data when you visit this
					website. The short version: it sets no cookies, runs no analytics
					and tracks nobody. The only processing is what any web host
					unavoidably does to deliver a page.
				</p>

				<h2>1. Scope</h2>
				<p>
					This policy covers <strong>this website only</strong> (the goloom
					marketing site and documentation). It does <strong>not</strong> cover
					the goloom software itself: when you download goloom and run it on
					your own infrastructure, <em>you</em> are the operator of that
					instance and the data controller for the accounts and content it
					processes. This site does not receive any data from self-hosted
					instances.
				</p>

				<h2>2. Controller</h2>
				<p>
					The controller responsible for this website within the meaning of
					the GDPR (Art. 4 No. 7) is:
				</p>
				<!-- TODO: replace with the responsible person or entity before publishing.
				     Under Art. 13 GDPR the controller's identity and a contact must be
				     given. This should be a single named person or legal entity (e.g. an
				     association), not the list of code contributors. -->
				<p class="lp-legal__box">
					<strong>[TODO: Name / legal entity]</strong><br />
					[TODO: Postal address]<br />
					Email: [TODO: contact email]
				</p>

				<h2>3. Hosting (GitHub Pages)</h2>
				<p>
					This site is served as static files by <strong>GitHub Pages</strong>,
					a service of GitHub, Inc. (88 Colin P. Kelly Jr. Street, San
					Francisco, CA 94107, USA), part of Microsoft. To deliver the pages,
					GitHub necessarily processes technical connection data — most
					notably your <strong>IP address</strong> — and may record it in
					server log files.
				</p>
				<p>
					We do not operate our own web server for this site and have no access
					to these logs. GitHub processes this data as our processor and under
					its own responsibility; see the
					<a href="https://docs.github.com/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement">GitHub Privacy Statement</a>.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR — our legitimate
					interest in presenting this project on a reliable, secure and
					low-maintenance platform.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>International transfer:</strong> GitHub is based in the USA,
					so data may be transferred there. GitHub relies on the EU Standard
					Contractual Clauses and its certification under the EU–US Data
					Privacy Framework as safeguards under Art. 44 ff. GDPR.
				</p>

				<h2>4. Server log data</h2>
				<p>
					When a page is requested, a web host typically processes: the
					requesting IP address, the date and time of the request, the page or
					file requested, the HTTP status, the referring page and the browser
					user-agent string. This is used to deliver content and to keep the
					service secure and functional. Retention and deletion of these logs
					are governed by GitHub, not by us.
				</p>

				<h2>5. No cookies, no tracking, no analytics</h2>
				<p>
					This site stores nothing on your device: no cookies, no local
					storage for tracking, no analytics or measurement tools, no
					advertising, no social-media pixels, and no third-party embeds that
					would profile you. Because nothing non-essential is stored or
					tracked, there is no consent banner — there is nothing to consent
					to.
				</p>

				<h2>6. Fonts and assets</h2>
				<p>
					Fonts and images are served from this same site, not from a
					third-party font or asset CDN. Loading a page therefore does not
					send your data to Google Fonts or any comparable service.
				</p>

				<h2>7. Contact by email</h2>
				<p>
					If you contact us by email, the address and the content of your
					message are processed solely to handle your request. Legal basis:
					Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (answering enquiries), or Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR where
					your request relates to a (pre-)contractual matter. The data is
					deleted once it is no longer needed and no retention obligations
					apply.
				</p>

				<h2>8. External links</h2>
				<p>
					This site links to external services such as the project on
					<a href={repo}>GitHub</a> and the social networks goloom supports.
					Once you follow such a link, the privacy policy of the respective
					provider applies; we have no influence over their processing.
				</p>

				<h2>9. Your rights</h2>
				<p>Under the GDPR you have the right to:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>access the data concerning you (Art. 15);</li>
					<li>rectification (Art. 16) and erasure (Art. 17);</li>
					<li>restriction of processing (Art. 18);</li>
					<li>data portability (Art. 20);</li>
					<li>object to processing based on legitimate interests (Art. 21).</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					To exercise these rights, contact the controller named above. Note
					that for the hosting log data described in section 3, requests are
					best directed to GitHub as the party that holds it.
				</p>

				<h2>10. Right to lodge a complaint</h2>
				<p>
					You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data-protection
					supervisory authority, in particular in the EU member state of your
					residence, place of work or the place of the alleged infringement,
					if you consider that the processing of your data infringes the GDPR.
				</p>

				<h2>11. Changes to this policy</h2>
				<p>
					We may update this policy to reflect changes to the site or the
					legal situation. The date at the top indicates the current version.
				</p>

				<p class="lp-legal__note">
					This page is provided in good faith for transparency and is not legal
					advice. The controller is responsible for its accuracy before
					publication.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<SiteFooter />
</LandingLayout>

<style>
	.lp-legal {
		max-width: 48rem;
	}
	.lp-legal h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
		margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
	}
	.lp-legal__meta {
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
	}
	.lp-legal h2 {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
		margin: 2.25rem 0 0.5rem;
	}
	.lp-legal p {
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
		line-height: 1.65;
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
	}
	.lp-legal ul {
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
		line-height: 1.65;
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		padding-left: 1.2rem;
	}
	.lp-legal li {
		margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
	}
	.lp-legal strong {
		color: var(--sl-color-white);
	}
	.lp-legal__box {
		border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
		background: var(--glass-bg);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 1rem 1.15rem;
	}
	.lp-legal__note {
		margin-top: 2.5rem;
		padding-top: 1.25rem;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
	}
	.lp-legal a {
		color: var(--brand-grad-from);
		text-decoration: none;
	}
	.lp-legal a:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}
</style>
